ire):","of Norman origin, a habitational name from Vaux (see   Vaux  ), a common French placename, singular and plural of <i>val</i> ‘valley’, the plural form being Latinized in surnames as <i>de Vallibus</i>. Norman lords with this surname are recorded in 12th- and early 13th-century records in Cumberland (Irthington), Devon (Farwood, in Colyton), East Yorkshire (Warter), Essex (Belchamp), and Leicestershire (Belvoir). Compare   Vale  .","nickname perhaps from Middle English <i>fals</i>, <i>faus</i>, <i>vaus</i> (Old French <i>fals</i>, <i>faus</i>, Old English <i>fals</i>) ‘deceitful, disloyal, dishonest, mendacious’, but it is more likely the name arises from 1, with the common Anglo-Norman French substitution of <i>le</i> for <i>de</i> in their surname."]}]},{"name":"Sibyl","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Sybil .  Even in classical times there was confusion between the two vowels in this word."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705192,"age":5,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705193,"age":14,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705195,"age":59,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Sibyl Vaux was born about 1323, in England. She married John Vaux before 1334, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"about 1323–":"umbes 1323–Surnud","1320–1349":"1320–1349","1334–1390":"1334–1390","1323–Female":"1323–Surnud","1349":"1349","1337":"1337","before 1334":"enne 1334","1334":"1334","1323":"1323","1453":"1453","1320":"1320","about 1323":"umbes 1323","1382":"1382","1390":"1390","1328":"1328","England":"England","Nottingham, Nottinghamshire, England":"Nottingham, Nottinghamshire, England"},"fi":{"about 1323–":"noin 1323–Kuollut","1320–1349":"1320–1349","1334–1390":"1334–1390","1323–Female":"1323–Kuollut","1349":"1349","1337":"1337","before 1334":"ennen vuotta 1334","1334":"1334","1323":"1323","1453":"1453","1320":"1320","about 1323":"noin 1323","1382":"1382","1390":"1390","1328":"1328","England":"England","Nottingham, Nottinghamshire, England":"Nottingham, Nottinghamshire, England"},"fr":{"about 1323–":"environ 1323–Décédée","1320–1349":"1320–1349","1334–1390":"1334–1390","1323–Female":"1323–Décédée","1349":"1349","1337":"1337","before 1334":"avant 1334","1334":"1334","1323":"1323","1453":"1453","1320":"1320","about 1323":"environ 1323","1382":"1382","1390":"1390","1328":"1328","England":"Angleterre","Nottingham, Nottinghamshire, England":"Nottingham, Nottinghamshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Mrs. Sibyl Vaux est née environ 1323, à Angleterre. Elle a épousé John Vaux avant 1334, à Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille."},"de":{"about 1323–":"um 1323–Verstorben","1320–1349":"1320–1349","1334–1390":"1334–1390","1323–Female":"1323–Verstorben","1349":"1349","1337":"1337","before 1334":"vor 1334","1334":"1334","1323":"1323","1453":"1453","1320":"1320","about 1323":"um 1323","1382":"1382","1390":"1390","1328":"1328","England":"England","Nottingham, Nottinghamshire, England":"Nott